value.0: The tall, curving horns upon this knight's helmet give him a rather intimidating air. He stands, stolid, unseen eyes watching from within the metal helm. Most people, you notice, avert their eyes and go out of their way to give this armored figure a wide berth.
One of Ostland's Everwatch Knights, this fellow stands firm, dark eyes watching all within range. Most people will avert their eyes and go out of their way to give this armored figure a wide berth.

A map of the Jarldom of Ostland. The town of Osthavn is in the southeast, decorated with an illustration of a sailing ship. From there, one road runs south off the map, another proceeding north along the coast for some distance before branching. The leftmost fork proceeds westward into the mountains - at its end is a castle, a crown depicted above it, labelled 'Ostdur'. A little further north and to the east is another fortress, shown perched on the edge of a sea cliff, with the name 'Rethgaard'. Finally, another road wends its way north through a hilly region to a small collection of houses or huts located on the north coast. The cartographer has not bothered to attach a name thereto.
This sturdy ladder ascends to a trap door in the ceiling and leads no doubt to the second floor of the tower.
A slender lever rises from the floor, controlling some unseen mechanism below.
The page bears the heading "Arrests" above a list of names, many of which have been crossed out.

A tall thin man of severe features and short black hair wearing scale mail and an ermine cloak glares out of the painting at you. This is the current Jarl (the Ruathymi title is 'Axe') of Ostland, Raorik Bathrie, depicted standing on the windswept battlements of a castle with mountain peaks in the near distance. Clearly this is his seat of power, the fortress of Ostdur.
